Package cscie160.hw5

Interface Summary
ATM ATM interface defines three functions, deposit, withdraw, and getBalance
ATMFactory Defines the ATMFactory, whose job it is to return a remote reference to an ATM
 

Class Summary
Account Account represents a bank account, and is essentially a wrapper around a float representing the account balance.
ATMFactoryImpl Implements ATMFactory, has a single method that returns a remote reference to an ATM when called
ATMImpl Represents a remote ATM object with three accounts stored in a Map, representing an account number and a corresponding account object
ATMProxy Client-side proxy class which manages the connection to the server and forwards the client's requests to the server by writing the text of requests to the stream on top of the socket established at creation time when the constructor is called.
Client  
Server The server process starts up, creates an ATMFactoryImpl instance, and registers it with the RMI.
TestATMFactory Tests the ATMFactoryImpl class
TestATMImpl TestATMImpl is analogous to TestATMImplementation in HW4.
 

Enum Summary
Commands  
 

Exception Summary
